result.execSummary:
The defendant Jordan J. Imm was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Fail/Report to Jail (Misdemeanor), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.425(1r)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: In the event probation is revoked, Defendant would be entitled to Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant to obtain a High School Diploma, GED or HSED during the pendency of probation term.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.

Defendant is ordered to participate in the Waushara County TAD/Safe Streets Program.    DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.   Defendant is to comply with any rules/recommendations as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Jordan J. Imm

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: 2:53 pm cases called. 15CF88, 16CF29 & 16CF30. Defendant Jordan J. Imm in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement reached. State moves to Amend Count 1 of 16CF29 to Fail to Report to Jail-Misd. in violation of 946.425(1r)(a). DA Blader makes statment regarding 15CF88. Attorney Szilagyi states the defendant is no longer contesting the request for 60 additional days jail. Court grants 60 day conditional jail.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Court accepts amendment as made by the State to Count 1 of 16CF29. Plea: Guilty to Count 1 of 16CF29 & Guilty to Count 2 of 16CF30.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in Count 2 of 16CF30.   Dismissal of repeater enhancer outright. Court sentences the defendant to: 16CF29-Impose 90 days WCJ, STAYED and places on probation for a period of 1 year, concurrent to 16CF30. If revoked, with Huber and Good Time Credit. CONDITIONS: Apply and begin participation in the Waushara County TAD Program.  Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.   The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. GED/HSED. Terms of Agent. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. 16CF30-SWD and places on Probation for a period of 30 months. CONDITIONS: Same as 16CF29 HOWEVER with Exceptions:  Defendant is ordered to participate and successfully complete the Waushara County TAD/Safe Streets Program. Early termination of probation after 24 months & successful completion of the TAD program and other conditions of probation.  DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. 15CF88-Defendant is no longer contesting conditional jail time on this mater. Court orders an amendment to JOC as previously signed of 60 days WCJ with Huber in 15CF88. Appeal Rights Given.

16CF29 & 16CF30 Cases called @ 1:18 p.m. Defendant Jordan J. Imm in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Defendant Jordan J. Imm in custody.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived. The Court entertains waiver of the preliminary hearing as to both matters. The Court accepts voluntary waiver of the preliminary hearing. Defendant BOT. Information filed by ADA Anderson. Receipt admitted - Reading waived.  NGP entered as to all counts.   STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.

15CF88 - Atty Szilagyi would like to request a clarification as to the imposition of conditional jail time requested by DOC - unsure as to how the conditional jail time was imposed as it was not originally ordered at the time of sentencing. The Court believes that the order may have been signed in error - a probation hearing should have taken place. The Court orders a probation review hearing be scheduled with the next hearing. If necessary the Court will vacate the Amended JOC at that time. Atty Szilagyi asks if the conditional jail sentence as ordered is with huber. The Court advises that the conditional jail sentence as the AJOC states is with huber.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for March 18, 2016 at 02:45 pm.

ALSO INCLUDES CASE NO. 16CF30. The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.
Defendant and Atty Szilagyi appear via video from the WC Jail.

16CF29 & 16CF30 Cases called @ 1:08 p.m. Defendant Jordan J. Imm in court, in custody, appears via video with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel. Defendant will be represented by SPD. ADA Anderson requesting $5000 Sig Bond. Atty Szilagyi takes no position on bond. Court orders $5000 Sig Bond.  IA Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State.  Initial appearance scheduled for February 23, 2016 at 01:15 pm.
